						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							The Aye-aye have a long middle finger, which it uses to tap on trees (8x per second!) to listen for insect larvae moving under the bark.  Once they locate it they use this same finger to scoop out their meal. Aye-ayes are secretive and love to move around at night to eat and socialize. They are the largest nocturnal primates in the world
						</text>
