						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Aye-ayes use their long middle fingers to tap tree trunks listening for insect larvae living under the bark. They will also eat fungi, fruit, and nuts. They spend hours and hours each night eating as much as they can. They can cover from 1 to 2 &#189; miles each night in order to eat.
						</text>
